explanation:
## Concept
Playwright provides user-centric locators that make tests more resilient to UI changes. getByRole() targets elements by their semantic meaning (button, link, etc.) while getByText() locates by visible text content.

## Implementation
```javascript
// getByRole - preferred for accessible testing
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' }).click();

// getByText - for text-based selection
await page.getByText('Welcome to dashboard').isVisible();

// Combining selectors
await page.getByRole('alert').getByText('Error occurred').isVisible();
```

## Trade-offs
**getByRole()**: More stable, accessibility-focused, but requires proper semantic HTML
**getByText()**: Direct but brittle to text changes, good for static content

## Pitfalls
- Avoid CSS selectors like $('.btn-primary') that break on style changes
- Use getByTestId() only when user-facing attributes aren't available
- getByRole() requires accessible markup to work effectively
